
# README_singleArtist (Run One Artist)

## When to Use This

Use this when you want a report for **one artist**.

---

## Step 1: Open Terminal

Navigate to the project folder:

```
cd MissingPieceMusicDashboard
```

---

## Step 2: Run the Artist Report

Basic command:

```
node scripts/runIngestAndExport.js "Artist Name"
```

Example:

```
node scripts/runIngestAndExport.js "Brian Dunne"
```

---

## Optional Options

### Include Track-Level Data

```
node scripts/runIngestAndExport.js "Brian Dunne" --tracks
```

### Choose Artist Manually (Recommended)

```
node scripts/runIngestAndExport.js "Brian Dunne" --interactive
```

---

## Where the File Goes

Your CSV will appear here:

```
outputExports/
Brian Dunne - Weekly Artist Tracking.csv
```

Open it in Excel or Google Sheets.

---

## If Something Goes Wrong

* If you see **jwt expired** â†’ refresh the token:

```
node scripts/exchange_chartmetric_token.js
```
OR
```
curl -d '{"refreshtoken":"YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN"}' -H "Content-Type: application/json" -X POST https://api.chartmetric.com/api/token
``` 
And copy paste token into .env

Then run the artist again.

---
